# Without this, `COPY . .` sweeps the whole working directory into the image and
# the build silently depends on whatever is lying around on the developer's
# machine. Concretely, all of these were shipping:
#
#   .env         dev DATABASE_URL and the placeholder ADMIN_COOKIE_SECRET, baked
#                into a production image. dotenv doesn't override real env vars
#                so it "worked" — but any deploy that lost its --env-file would
#                quietly fall back to a cookie secret that is public knowledge.
#   node_modules the HOST's modules, copied over the ones npm ci had just
#                installed, native Prisma engine and all.
#   .adminjs     AdminJS's build cache. This one hid a real bug: the image had a
#                writable .adminjs only because the developer had run the app
#                locally, so it worked here and EACCES'd in CI, where the
#                checkout is clean.
#   .git         the entire history, for no reason.

.env
.env.*
!.env.example

node_modules
.adminjs

.git
.gitignore
.github

README.md
Dockerfile
.dockerignore

npm-debug.log*
*.log
